<p>Bad mobile signals and unreliable hotspot coverage on your iPhone could well be two of the most frustrating challenges <a href="https://blogs.computerworld.com/article/3646553/17-ways-the-iphone-transformed-enterprise-tech.html" rel="nofollow">today’s enterprise professionals</a> face (other than <a href="https://www.computerworld.com/article/3488497/10-tips-for-better-iphone-battery-life.html">battery life</a>). Here are some ways that may improve network coverage and hotspot reliability, making it easier to get work done while on the go.</p><h2><strong>How to improve your network signal</strong></h2>
